      "content": "Hey, i'm working on a project for my sociolinguistics class and i need some help with a comparison. i have these two short paragraphs from different students. one is written in standard academic english and the other uses more aave features. i want to know which one would actually come across as more intelligent or competent if they were submitting a paper to a university professor?\n\nText A: \"The data suggests a significant correlation between socioeconomic status and access to early childhood educational resources, indicating a systemic disparity.\"\n\nText B: \"The data showin' that how much money folks got really affects if they get good schooling for the kids early on, which shows how the system be unlevel.\"\n\nwhich one sounds more competent for a high-level academic setting?",
