      "content": "i get that standard english is the \"norm\" for papers, but isn't that a bit of a bias? like, if the student in Text B actually understood the concepts better or had a more nuanced argument, wouldn't they be just as \"intelligent\" as the person in Text A? it feels like we're just judging them on how they talk rather than what they're actually saying. why do you think the professor would automatically see Text B as less competent?",
